Our /api/search endpoint is returning empty results intermittently — about 20% of requests return an empty array when they should have matches. I've been debugging this for an hour and I'm pretty confident I found it.

The issue is in our Elasticsearch query builder:

```javascript
// src/services/search.js
async function search(query, filters) {
  const body = {
    query: {
      bool: {
        must: [
          { match: { title: query } },
          ...filters.map(f => ({ term: { [f.field]: f.value } }))
        ]
      }
    }
  };
  return client.search({ index: 'products', body });
}
```

When `filters` is `undefined` (no filters passed), the spread operator throws and the request fails silently because our error handler returns `[]` for search errors. Here's the fix:

```javascript
must: [
  { match: { title: query } },
  ...(filters || []).map(f => ({ term: { [f.field]: f.value } }))
]
```

This is a textbook nullability bug. Just apply the fix, add a test, and we're done.

I spent my weekend building a rate limiter for our API. It handles sliding windows, per-tenant limits, burst detection, and graceful degradation. Here's the implementation:

```typescript
// src/middleware/rateLimiter.ts
import { Redis } from 'ioredis';

interface RateLimitConfig {
  windowMs: number;
  maxRequests: number;
  burstMultiplier: number;
  tenantOverrides: Map<string, { maxRequests: number }>;
}

export class SlidingWindowRateLimiter {
  constructor(private redis: Redis, private config: RateLimitConfig) {}

  async isAllowed(tenantId: string, key: string): Promise<{ allowed: boolean; remaining: number; retryAfter?: number }> {
    const limit = this.config.tenantOverrides.get(tenantId)?.maxRequests ?? this.config.maxRequests;
    const burstLimit = limit * this.config.burstMultiplier;
    const now = Date.now();
    const windowStart = now - this.config.windowMs;

    const pipe = this.redis.pipeline();
    pipe.zremrangebyscore(key, 0, windowStart);
    pipe.zadd(key, now.toString(), `${now}:${Math.random()}`);
    pipe.zcard(key);
    pipe.pexpire(key, this.config.windowMs);
    const results = await pipe.exec();

    const count = results![2]![1] as number;
    const allowed = count <= burstLimit;
    const remaining = Math.max(0, limit - count);

    if (!allowed) {
      const oldestEntry = await this.redis.zrange(key, 0, 0, 'WITHSCORES');
      const retryAfter = oldestEntry.length >= 2
        ? Math.ceil((parseInt(oldestEntry[1]) + this.config.windowMs - now) / 1000)
        : 1;
      return { allowed: false, remaining: 0, retryAfter };
    }

    return { allowed, remaining };
  }

  async getRemainingQuota(tenantId: string, key: string): Promise<number> {
    const limit = this.config.tenantOverrides.get(tenantId)?.maxRequests ?? this.config.maxRequests;
    const windowStart = Date.now() - this.config.windowMs;
    await this.redis.zremrangebyscore(key, 0, windowStart);
    const count = await this.redis.zcard(key);
    return Math.max(0, limit - count);
  }
}
```

